WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:23.842
My name is H.I. McDunnough.

2
00:00:27.264 --> 00:00:28.432
Call me Hi.

3
00:00:30.810 --> 00:00:32.103
The first time I met Ed...

4
00:00:32.145 --> 00:00:34.773
was in the county lockup in Tempe. Arizona.

5
00:00:36.860 --> 00:00:38.445
Don't forget his profile. Ed.

6
00:00:38.487 --> 00:00:39.655
Turn to the right!

7
00:00:39.697 --> 00:00:41.407
The day I'll never forget.

8
00:00:43.035 --> 00:00:44.244
Turn to the right!

9
00:00:44.287 --> 00:00:47.165
What kind of name is Ed for a pretty thing like you?

10
00:00:47.207 --> 00:00:49.167
Short for Edwina. Turn to the right!

11
00:00:49.794 --> 00:00:50.962
You're a flower. you are.

12
00:00:52.381 --> 00:00:54.508
Just a little desert flower.

13
00:00:55.969 --> 00:00:57.846
Let me know how those come out.

14
00:00:58.764 --> 00:01:01.183
Prison life is very structured...

15
00:01:01.226 --> 00:01:03.854
more than most people care for...

16
00:01:03.896 --> 00:01:06.733
but there's a spirit of camaraderie between the men...

17
00:01:06.734 --> 00:01:09.404
like you find only in combat. maybe...

18
00:01:09.446 --> 00:01:12.867
or on a pro ball club in the heat of the pennant drive.

19
00:01:14.577 --> 00:01:16.537
In an effort to better ourselves...

20
00:01:16.580 --> 00:01:18.457
we were forced to meet with a counselor...

21
00:01:18.499 --> 00:01:22.796
who tried to help us figure out why we were the way we were.

22
00:01:22.839 --> 00:01:25.926
All he wanted was a hot roll and butter.

23
00:01:25.968 --> 00:01:27.636
So...

24
00:01:27.679 --> 00:01:30.182
why do you use the word "trapped"?

25
00:01:31.559 --> 00:01:35.981
Why do you say you feel trapped in a man's body?

26
00:01:37.066 --> 00:01:40.612
Well. sometimes I get the menstrual cramps real hard.

27
00:01:40.654 --> 00:01:42.781
Have you learned anything. Hi?

28
00:01:42.824 --> 00:01:44.367
Yes. sir. You bet.

29
00:01:44.410 --> 00:01:46.496
You wouldn't lie to us. would you?

30
00:01:46.537 --> 00:01:49.082
No. ma'am. Hope to say.

31
00:01:49.124 --> 00:01:50.375
OK. then.

32
00:01:51.043 --> 00:01:53.755
I tried to stand up and fly straight...

33
00:01:53.797 --> 00:01:57.218
but it wasn't easy with Reagan in the White House.

34
00:01:59.263 --> 00:02:00.431
I don't know.

35
00:02:01.516 --> 00:02:04.019
They say he's a decent man. so...

36
00:02:05.229 --> 00:02:07.440
maybe his advisers are confused.

37
00:02:10.486 --> 00:02:12.405
Turn to the right.

38
00:02:14.450 --> 00:02:15.785
What's the matter. Ed?

39
00:02:17.997 --> 00:02:19.624
My "fy- ance" left me.

40
00:02:19.666 --> 00:02:21.209
She said her fiance had run off...

41
00:02:21.251 --> 00:02:22.836
with a student cosmetologist...

42
00:02:22.878 --> 00:02:25.131
who knew how to ply her feminine wiles.

43
00:02:26.007 --> 00:02:27.801
The sumbitch.

44
00:02:27.843 --> 00:02:29.678
Don't forget his phone call. Ed.

45
00:02:30.680 --> 00:02:34.351
Tell him I think he's a damn fool. Ed.

46
00:02:34.894 --> 00:02:37.856
You tell him I said so...

47
00:02:37.857 --> 00:02:39.734
H.I. McDunnough.

48
00:02:39.776 --> 00:02:42.738
If he wants to discuss it. he knows where to find me...

49
00:02:42.780 --> 00:02:44.907
in the Maricopa County Maximum Security...

50
00:02:44.950 --> 00:02:46.493
Correctional Facility For Men...

51
00:02:46.535 --> 00:02:49.080
State Farm Road Number Thirty- one. Tempe. Arizona!

52
00:02:49.122 --> 00:02:50.331
I'll be waitin'!

53
00:02:51.959 --> 00:02:53.127
I'll be waitin'.

54
00:02:55.339 --> 00:02:59.010
I can't say I was happy to be back inside...

55
00:02:59.052 --> 00:03:02.973
but the flood of familiar sights. sounds. and faces...

56
00:03:03.016 --> 00:03:05.394
almost made it feel like a homecoming.

57
00:03:05.436 --> 00:03:08.690
Most men your age are getting married and raising a family.

58
00:03:08.732 --> 00:03:09.941
Well. factually...

59
00:03:09.984 --> 00:03:12.028
They wouldn't accept prison as a substitute.

60
00:03:13.238 --> 00:03:14.781
Would any of you men care to comment?

61
00:03:16.743 --> 00:03:19.496
sometimes your career has got to come before family.

62
00:03:20.164 --> 00:03:22.083
Work's what's kept us happy.

63
00:03:22.083 --> 00:03:25.921
I tried to sort through what Doc Schwartz had said...

64
00:03:25.964 --> 00:03:28.968
but prison ain't the easiest place to think.

65
00:03:29.009 --> 00:03:32.263
When there was no meat. we ate fowl.

66
00:03:32.305 --> 00:03:35.309
When there was no fowl. we ate crawdad.

67
00:03:35.351 --> 00:03:38.897
When there was no crawdad to be found. we ate sand.

68
00:03:38.939 --> 00:03:41.692
- You ate what? - We ate sand.

69
00:03:41.735 --> 00:03:44.655
- You ate sand? - That's right.

70
00:03:44.697 --> 00:03:46.824
Well. Hi. you done served your twenty months...

71
00:03:46.867 --> 00:03:49.286
and seeing as how you never use live ammo...

72
00:03:49.328 --> 00:03:52.415
we got no choice but to return you to society.

73
00:03:52.458 --> 00:03:54.794
These doors gonna swing wide.

74
00:03:54.794 --> 00:03:57.714
I didn't want to hurt anyone. sir.

75
00:03:57.757 --> 00:03:59.217
Hi. we respect that.

76
00:03:59.259 --> 00:04:00.677
But you're just hurting yourself...

77
00:04:00.719 --> 00:04:02.638
with this rambunctious behavior.

78
00:04:02.638 --> 00:04:04.640
I know that. sir.

79
00:04:04.683 --> 00:04:05.976
OK. then.

80
00:04:06.018 --> 00:04:07.478
I don't know how you come down...

81
00:04:07.520 --> 00:04:09.439
on the incarceration question...

82
00:04:09.481 --> 00:04:12.651
whether it's for rehabilitation or revenge...

83
00:04:12.693 --> 00:04:14.487
but I was beginning to think...

84
00:04:14.487 --> 00:04:17.324
revenge is the only argument makes any sense.

85
00:04:20.037 --> 00:04:21.664
Show the tattoo!

86
00:04:22.832 --> 00:04:24.334
Turn to the right!

87
00:04:24.376 --> 00:04:25.878
Don't forget his fingers. Ed.

88
00:04:27.463 --> 00:04:28.839
Hear about the paddy wagon...

89
00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:31.259
that collided with the cement mixer. Ed?

90
00:04:32.178 --> 00:04:34.681
Twelve hardened criminals escaped.

91
00:04:35.474 --> 00:04:37.810
Ha ha! I heard that one.

92
00:04:37.852 --> 00:04:39.187
Got a new beau?

93
00:04:39.229 --> 00:04:41.023
No. Hi. I sure don't.

94
00:04:42.567 --> 00:04:45.195
Don't worry. I paid for it.

95
00:04:45.237 --> 00:04:48.199
They say that absence makes the heart grow fonder.

96
00:04:49.535 --> 00:04:51.621
And for once. they may be right.

97
00:04:51.663 --> 00:04:53.707
- You missed a spot. - Rrr!

98
00:04:53.749 --> 00:04:56.961
More and more. my thoughts turned to Ed...

99
00:04:57.003 --> 00:05:00.674
and I finally felt the pain of imprisonment.

100
00:05:00.717 --> 00:05:02.302
Mama would throw the live crawdad...

101
00:05:02.344 --> 00:05:05.014
in a pan of boiling water.

102
00:05:05.056 --> 00:05:08.310
One day. I decided to make my own crawdad...

103
00:05:08.352 --> 00:05:12.732
and I threw it in a pot without the water. you see?

104
00:05:12.775 --> 00:05:14.861
And it was just like making popcorn.

105
00:05:16.405 --> 00:05:18.407
Yeah. the joint is a lonely place...

106
00:05:18.449 --> 00:05:20.868
after lockup and lights out...

107
00:05:20.911 --> 00:05:22.037
when the last of the cons...

108
00:05:22.079 --> 00:05:24.624
has been swept away by the sandman.

109
00:05:25.417 --> 00:05:26.835
But I couldn't help thinking...

110
00:05:26.877 --> 00:05:29.046
that a brighter future lay ahead...

111
00:05:30.882 --> 00:05:34.386
a future that was only eight to fourteen months away.

112
00:05:39.561 --> 00:05:42.690
They got a name for people like you. Hi.

113
00:05:42.732 --> 00:05:45.360
That name is called recidivism.

114
00:05:45.402 --> 00:05:47.279
Repeat offender.

115
00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:49.366
Not a pretty name. is it. Hi?

116
00:05:49.408 --> 00:05:51.535
No. sir. That's one bonehead name...

117
00:05:51.577 --> 00:05:52.870
but that ain't me anymore.

118
00:05:52.912 --> 00:05:55.582
You're not just telling us what we want to hear?

119
00:05:55.624 --> 00:05:57.376
No. sir. No way.

120
00:05:57.418 --> 00:05:59.587
'Cause we just want to hear the truth.

121
00:05:59.630 --> 00:06:02.842
Then I guess I am telling you what you want to hear.

122
00:06:02.884 --> 00:06:05.387
Didn't we just tell you not to do that?

123
00:06:05.429 --> 00:06:07.056
Yes. sir.

124
00:06:07.098 --> 00:06:08.433
OK. then.

125
00:06:09.268 --> 00:06:10.436
Turn to the right!

126
00:06:11.354 --> 00:06:13.523
I'm walking in here on my knees. Ed...

127
00:06:13.565 --> 00:06:15.067
a free man proposing.

128
00:06:15.109 --> 00:06:16.485
Howdy. Kurt.

129
00:06:16.528 --> 00:06:17.946
And so it was.

130
00:06:17.946 --> 00:06:19.948
Don't forget the bouquet. Ed.

131
00:06:20.908 --> 00:06:22.034
I do.

132
00:06:22.077 --> 00:06:23.328
You bet I do.

133
00:06:23.370 --> 00:06:25.038
OK. then.

134
00:06:28.752 --> 00:06:31.213
Ed's pa staked us to a starter home...

135
00:06:31.298 --> 00:06:32.591
in suburban Tempe...

136
00:06:32.633 --> 00:06:35.595
and I got a job drilling holes in sheet metal.

137
00:06:35.637 --> 00:06:37.556
We were doing paramedical work...

138
00:06:37.598 --> 00:06:39.642
in affiliation with the state highway system.

139
00:06:39.684 --> 00:06:41.853
Not actually practicing. you understand.

140
00:06:41.895 --> 00:06:44.440
Me and Bill were patrolling down Nine Mile.

141
00:06:44.482 --> 00:06:47.277
- Bill Roberts? - No. not that mother- scratcher.

142
00:06:47.319 --> 00:06:49.446
Bill Parker.

143
00:06:49.489 --> 00:06:51.742
Anyway. we're approaching the wreck...

144
00:06:51.784 --> 00:06:53.578
and there's this spherical object...

145
00:06:53.619 --> 00:06:55.955
resting in the highway...

146
00:06:55.998 --> 00:06:58.042
and it's not a piece of the car.

147
00:06:58.084 --> 00:07:00.962
Most ways. the job was a lot like prison...

148
00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:04.592
except Ed was waiting at the end of every day...

149
00:07:04.634 --> 00:07:06.636
and a paycheck at the end of every week.

150
00:07:06.679 --> 00:07:09.098
Government do take a bite. don't she?

151
00:07:10.392 --> 00:07:12.352
These were the happy days...

152
00:07:12.353 --> 00:07:15.148
the salad days. as they say.

153
00:07:15.190 --> 00:07:19.111
Ed felt that having a critter was the next logical step.

154
00:07:19.154 --> 00:07:21.991
It was all she thought about.

155
00:07:22.033 --> 00:07:24.870
Her point was that there was too much love and beauty...

156
00:07:24.912 --> 00:07:27.165
for just the two of us...

157
00:07:27.206 --> 00:07:29.584
and every day we kept a child out of the world...

158
00:07:29.626 --> 00:07:32.379
was a day he might later regret having missed.

159
00:07:35.259 --> 00:07:37.219
That was beautiful.

160
00:07:37.220 --> 00:07:41.016
So we worked at it on the days we calculated most likely to be fruitful...

161
00:07:41.768 --> 00:07:45.022
and we worked at it most other days. just to be sure.

162
00:07:45.648 --> 00:07:48.860
Ed rejoiced that my lawless years were behind me...

163
00:07:48.902 --> 00:07:50.946
and that our child- rearing years lay ahead.

164
00:07:52.157 --> 00:07:53.742
And then the roof caved in.

165
00:08:00.126 --> 00:08:01.335
Hi...

166
00:08:02.588 --> 00:08:03.756
I'm barren!

167
00:08:04.924 --> 00:08:06.968
At first I didn't believe it...

168
00:08:07.010 --> 00:08:09.221
that this woman who looked as fertile...

169
00:08:09.263 --> 00:08:10.890
as the Tennessee Valley...

170
00:08:10.932 --> 00:08:12.267
could not bear children.

171
00:08:13.477 --> 00:08:15.479
But the doctor explained that her insides...

172
00:08:15.522 --> 00:08:19.235
were a rocky place where my seed could find no purchase.

173
00:08:22.197 --> 00:08:23.740
Ed was inconsolable.

174
00:08:25.410 --> 00:08:27.454
We tried an adoption agency.

175
00:08:28.957 --> 00:08:32.127
It's true that Hi has had a checkered past.

176
00:08:32.169 --> 00:08:35.423
But Ed here is an officer of the law twice decorated...

177
00:08:35.465 --> 00:08:37.759
so we figure it kind of evens out.

178
00:08:41.140 --> 00:08:44.018
But biology and the prejudices of others...

179
00:08:44.060 --> 00:08:45.937
conspired to keep us childless.

180
00:08:49.067 --> 00:08:51.445
Our love for each other was stronger than ever...

181
00:08:52.488 --> 00:08:56.743
but I premonised no return of the salad days.

182
00:08:57.662 --> 00:08:59.915
The pizzazz had gone out of our lives.

183
00:09:01.167 --> 00:09:03.962
Ed lost all interest in both criminal justice...

184
00:09:04.713 --> 00:09:06.966
and housekeeping.

185
00:09:07.008 --> 00:09:10.763
Soon after. she tendered her badge.

186
00:09:10.805 --> 00:09:13.975
Even my job seemed as dry and bitter...

187
00:09:14.018 --> 00:09:15.978
as a hot prairie wind.

188
00:09:16.020 --> 00:09:18.732
So here's Bill walking down Nine Mile...

189
00:09:18.774 --> 00:09:20.734
That's Bill Parker. you understand.

190
00:09:20.777 --> 00:09:23.739
He's got his sandwich in one hand...

191
00:09:23.781 --> 00:09:26.200
and the fuckin' head in the other!

192
00:09:28.996 --> 00:09:32.250
I even caught myself driving by convenience stores...

193
00:09:33.627 --> 00:09:35.546
that weren't on the way home.

194
00:09:37.383 --> 00:09:38.968
Then. one day...

195
00:09:39.677 --> 00:09:42.931
the biggest news hit the state since they built the Hoover Dam.

196
00:09:45.477 --> 00:09:47.354
The Arizona Quints was born.

197
00:09:48.397 --> 00:09:51.401
By Arizona Quints...

198
00:09:51.401 --> 00:09:56.073
I mean they was born to a woman named Florence Arizona.

199
00:09:56.116 --> 00:09:57.618
As you probably guessed...

200
00:09:57.660 --> 00:10:01.123
Florence Arizona is the wife of Nathan Arizona...

201
00:10:01.916 --> 00:10:03.042
and Nathan Arizona...

202
00:10:03.960 --> 00:10:06.838
well. hell. you know who he is.

203
00:10:06.881 --> 00:10:10.302
So come on down to Unpainted Arizona...

204
00:10:10.344 --> 00:10:11.804
where you can get the finest selection...

205
00:10:11.846 --> 00:10:13.723
in fixtures and appointments...

206
00:10:13.765 --> 00:10:16.393
for your bathroom. bedroom. boudoir!

207
00:10:16.435 --> 00:10:19.272
And if you can find lower prices anywhere...

208
00:10:19.314 --> 00:10:21.817
my name ain't Nathan Arizona!

209
00:10:21.859 --> 00:10:24.529
The owner of the largest chain of unpainted furniture...

210
00:10:24.571 --> 00:10:29.077
and bathroom fixture outlets throughout the Southwest.

211
00:10:29.119 --> 00:10:32.498
Yep. Florence had been taking fertility pills...

212
00:10:32.540 --> 00:10:34.751
and she and Nathan had hit the jackpot.

213
00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:37.294


214
00:10:37.297 --> 00:10:42.178
Now. y'all without sin can cast the first stone...

215
00:10:43.138 --> 00:10:46.142
but we thought it was unfair that some should have so many...

216
00:10:46.184 --> 00:10:48.395
while others should have so few.

217
00:10:50.189 --> 00:10:52.316
With the benefit of hindsight...

218
00:10:52.359 --> 00:10:54.486
maybe it wasn't such a hot idea.

219
00:10:56.156 --> 00:10:58.283
But at the time...

220
00:10:58.325 --> 00:11:00.369
Ed's little plan seemed like the solution...

221
00:11:00.411 --> 00:11:02.538
to all our problems...

222
00:11:02.581 --> 00:11:05.668
and the answer to all our prayers.

223
00:11:39.005 --> 00:11:42.259
Eight hundred leaf- tables and no chairs?

224
00:11:42.301 --> 00:11:44.929
You can't sell leaf- tables and no chairs.

225
00:11:44.972 --> 00:11:48.351
Chairs. you got a dinette set. No chairs. you got dick!

226
00:11:48.393 --> 00:11:50.312
I asked my wife. She got more sense.

227
00:11:52.023 --> 00:11:54.067
Miles. alls I know is...

228
00:11:54.109 --> 00:11:56.654
I'm away from the office to play with my kids...

229
00:11:56.696 --> 00:11:58.740
and everything goes straight to heck!

230
00:11:58.782 --> 00:12:00.450
I ain't gonna stand for it!

231
00:12:02.036 --> 00:12:04.956
Yeah. if a frog had wings. it wouldn't bump its ass a- hoppin'.

232
00:12:04.999 --> 00:12:07.544
I am sick of your excuses. Miles.

233
00:12:08.420 --> 00:12:10.422
It is now precisely...

234
00:12:10.465 --> 00:12:13.635
8:45 in the p.m.

235
00:12:13.677 --> 00:12:16.222
I'm gonna be down at that store in exactly twelve hours...

236
00:12:16.264 --> 00:12:18.433
to kick me some butt...

237
00:12:18.475 --> 00:12:20.435
or my name ain't Nathan Arizona!

238
00:12:25.527 --> 00:12:27.070
That sounds like Larry.

239
00:12:27.112 --> 00:12:30.074
No. no. no. Shh. Shh.

240
00:12:32.620 --> 00:12:34.205
Quiet. quiet. quiet.

241
00:12:37.960 --> 00:12:39.503
Quiet. quiet.

242
00:12:41.131 --> 00:12:42.633
Quiet.

243
00:12:42.633 --> 00:12:43.801
Good boy.

244
00:12:48.766 --> 00:12:49.934
Quiet. quiet.

245
00:12:56.026 --> 00:12:57.820
That's it. Good. good.

246
00:12:59.698 --> 00:13:00.866
Quiet.

247
00:13:05.456 --> 00:13:06.624
Yes.

248
00:13:16.095 --> 00:13:17.304
Here's a rattle.

249
00:13:17.347 --> 00:13:18.682
Rattle. OK?

250
00:13:18.724 --> 00:13:20.100
OK. good.

251
00:13:35.872 --> 00:13:37.290
No. no.

252
00:13:37.332 --> 00:13:39.835
Shh. Shh. Quiet. quiet.

253
00:13:54.230 --> 00:13:55.398
Come here.

254
00:14:48.470 --> 00:14:51.098
Come here. Come here.

255
00:15:31.695 --> 00:15:34.198
Why don't you go up and check on them?

256
00:15:34.240 --> 00:15:35.408
They sound restless.

257
00:16:20.136 --> 00:16:21.429
What's the matter?

258
00:16:21.471 --> 00:16:23.640
I'm sorry. honey. It just didn't work out.

259
00:16:23.682 --> 00:16:25.225
What do you mean it didn't work out?

260
00:16:25.267 --> 00:16:29.105
They...they started crying.

261
00:16:29.148 --> 00:16:30.816
They were all over me.

262
00:16:30.858 --> 00:16:32.902
It was kind of horrifying. honey. Let me in.

263
00:16:32.945 --> 00:16:34.238
Of course they cried. Babies cry.

264
00:16:34.280 --> 00:16:37.284
I know that. We better leave.

265
00:16:37.325 --> 00:16:39.035
You go right back up there and get me a toddler.

266
00:16:39.078 --> 00:16:41.915
I need a baby. Hi. They got more than they can handle.

267
