01:09:01.682 --> 01:09:03.142
Six Mississippi...

1055
01:09:03.184 --> 01:09:04.644
seven Mississippi...

1056
01:09:04.645 --> 01:09:06.272
eight Mississippi...

1057
01:09:06.314 --> 01:09:07.482
nine Mississippi...

1058
01:09:07.524 --> 01:09:10.486
Got some baby grub. baby wipes.

1059
01:09:10.528 --> 01:09:12.822
Got them diapers. them disposable kind.

1060
01:09:12.865 --> 01:09:14.241
I got me a packet of balloons.

1061
01:09:14.283 --> 01:09:16.160
They blow up into funny shapes?

1062
01:09:16.203 --> 01:09:17.830
No. Just circular.

1063
01:09:17.872 --> 01:09:20.375
Say...where's Junior?

1064
01:09:20.417 --> 01:09:23.463
- Didn't you put him in? - I thought...

1065
01:09:25.967 --> 01:09:27.218
Where did we leave him?

1066
01:09:45.244 --> 01:09:46.454
No!

1067
01:10:07.109 --> 01:10:09.070
- My baby! - Aah!

1068
01:10:10.739 --> 01:10:13.701
Eight hundred one Mississippi.

1069
01:10:13.743 --> 01:10:15.704
Eight hundred Mississippi...

1070
01:10:22.172 --> 01:10:24.550
- Aah! - Junior!

1071
01:10:26.219 --> 01:10:29.932
- Aah! Aah! - We're on the way!

1072
01:10:29.975 --> 01:10:32.103
Seven hundred and ninety- one...

1073
01:10:32.145 --> 01:10:34.147
Aw. bullshit!

1074
01:10:40.615 --> 01:10:43.368
Seven hundred and ninety- aught Mississippi...

1075
01:10:48.209 --> 01:10:50.462
Seven hundred eighty- seven Mississippi...

1076
01:10:50.504 --> 01:10:54.467
Oh. baby! Oh. baby.

1077
01:10:54.510 --> 01:10:56.512
Seven hundred eighty- five Mississippi...

1078
01:10:56.554 --> 01:11:00.559
Promise we ain't never gonna leave him. Gale.

1079
01:11:00.602 --> 01:11:04.232
We ain't never gonna give him up again. Evelle.

1080
01:11:04.274 --> 01:11:06.109
He's our little Gale Junior now.

1081
01:11:20.714 --> 01:11:21.882
Ed...

1082
01:11:25.346 --> 01:11:27.724
I realize...

1083
01:11:27.766 --> 01:11:32.272
I can't be much of a comfort to you now...

1084
01:11:34.525 --> 01:11:36.653
but let me just say this.

1085
01:11:38.573 --> 01:11:40.367
You'll feel a whole lot better...

1086
01:11:40.409 --> 01:11:42.870
- I don't want to feel better. - Honey.

1087
01:11:42.912 --> 01:11:45.665
I don't care about myself anymore.

1088
01:11:45.708 --> 01:11:47.460
I don't care about us anymore.

1089
01:11:48.963 --> 01:11:50.924
I just want Nathan Junior back safe.

1090
01:11:50.965 --> 01:11:52.133
I know that.

1091
01:11:52.176 --> 01:11:55.305
If we don't get him back. I don't want to go on living.

1092
01:11:55.347 --> 01:12:00.562
Even if we do get him back. I don't want to live with you.

1093
01:12:09.200 --> 01:12:12.162
I...I guess I still love you. Hi.

1094
01:12:12.997 --> 01:12:15.917
I...I know I do.

1095
01:12:15.960 --> 01:12:17.503
I ain't even blamin' you.

1096
01:12:17.545 --> 01:12:21.759
The whole thing was crazy. and the whole thing was my idea.

1097
01:12:21.801 --> 01:12:24.847
Factually. I bear a large percentage...

1098
01:12:24.889 --> 01:12:26.057
Let me finish.

1099
01:12:27.351 --> 01:12:29.437
Ever since those jailbirds took Nathan...

1100
01:12:29.479 --> 01:12:33.109
I been doin' some thinkin'. and I ain't too proud of myself.

1101
01:12:33.151 --> 01:12:38.491
Even if Mrs. Arizona had more than she could handle...

1102
01:12:38.533 --> 01:12:44.249
I was a police officer sworn to uphold the Constitution of the United States.

1103
01:12:44.292 --> 01:12:46.420
You resigned before we ever...

1104
01:12:46.461 --> 01:12:48.547
That ain't the point. Hi.

1105
01:12:48.589 --> 01:12:50.383
We don't deserve Nathan Junior...

1106
01:12:50.425 --> 01:12:52.594
any more than those jailbirds do.

1107
01:12:53.972 --> 01:12:57.268
If I'm as selfish and irresponsible as you...

1108
01:12:57.310 --> 01:12:58.645
You're not that bad.

1109
01:12:58.687 --> 01:13:01.649
If I'm as bad as you. what good are we to each other?

1110
01:13:04.320 --> 01:13:06.865
You and me's just a fool's paradise.

1111
01:13:38.320 --> 01:13:43.165


1112
01:13:56.395 --> 01:13:58.189
- There she is. - Yep.

1113
01:13:59.065 --> 01:14:01.610
Well. let's do her.

1114
01:14:02.403 --> 01:14:04.531
What are we gonna do with Gale Junior?

1115
01:14:04.573 --> 01:14:05.824
He stays here.

1116
01:14:05.867 --> 01:14:07.494
Are you crazy?

1117
01:14:07.536 --> 01:14:10.123
Suppose we go in there and get ourselves killed?

1118
01:14:10.164 --> 01:14:12.292
It would be hours before he gets discovered.

1119
01:14:14.420 --> 01:14:16.673
All right. you hayseeds. it's a stickup!

1120
01:14:17.258 --> 01:14:18.885
Everybody freeze.

1121
01:14:18.927 --> 01:14:20.637
Everybody down on the ground.

1122
01:14:26.605 --> 01:14:28.816
Well. which is it. young feller?

1123
01:14:28.858 --> 01:14:31.653
You want I should freeze or get down on the ground?

1124
01:14:31.695 --> 01:14:36.410
I mean to say. if'n I freeze. I can't rightly drop.

1125
01:14:36.452 --> 01:14:39.080
If'n I drop. I'm gonna be in motion.

1126
01:14:39.122 --> 01:14:41.750
- Shut up! - OK. then.

1127
01:14:41.793 --> 01:14:43.879
Everybody down on the ground!

1128
01:14:43.921 --> 01:14:46.215
Forget that part about freezing. now.

1129
01:14:46.258 --> 01:14:49.804
- Till they get down there. - Y'all hear that. don't you?

1130
01:14:49.846 --> 01:14:51.932
Want to fill this up. partner?

1131
01:14:51.974 --> 01:14:54.394
We gotta...Shit!

1132
01:14:54.436 --> 01:14:56.105
Where'd all the tellers go?

1133
01:14:56.147 --> 01:14:57.690
Down here. sir.

1134
01:14:57.732 --> 01:15:00.778
They're on the ground like you commanded. Gale.

1135
01:15:01.822 --> 01:15:04.116
I told you not to use my damn name.

1136
01:15:04.158 --> 01:15:06.536
Can't you try to keep from forgetting that?

1137
01:15:09.457 --> 01:15:11.292
Not even your code name?

1138
01:15:12.962 --> 01:15:15.590
Oh. yeah. yeah. My code name.

1139
01:15:15.633 --> 01:15:18.762
Y'all hear that? We're using code names.

1140
01:15:18.804 --> 01:15:22.058
We're just about ready to begin the robbery proper!

1141
01:15:27.525 --> 01:15:30.070
Hurry up. you dang hayseed!

1142
01:15:30.112 --> 01:15:33.783
All right. Now. y'all know how this here works.

1143
01:15:33.826 --> 01:15:36.830
And that hayseed over there with the red hat...

1144
01:15:36.872 --> 01:15:38.457
he's the monitor.

1145
01:15:38.499 --> 01:15:39.834
OK. you betcha.

1146
01:15:42.213 --> 01:15:45.509
I want you to stay flat for ten full minutes!

1147
01:15:45.551 --> 01:15:48.263
We might just come back in five to check.

1148
01:15:48.305 --> 01:15:50.808
That's for us to know. and y'all to find out.

1149
01:15:50.850 --> 01:15:53.395
Anyone found bipedal in five wears his ass for a hat.

1150
01:16:05.746 --> 01:16:08.458
That old- timer threw off my concentration...

1151
01:16:09.209 --> 01:16:11.044
otherwise. it would've gone smoother.

1152
01:16:11.087 --> 01:16:12.797
Shoot. Gale. we done good.

1153
01:16:12.840 --> 01:16:15.510
This ought to split up nice three ways.

1154
01:16:19.641 --> 01:16:22.228
God damn it! You never leave a man behind!

1155
01:16:47.431 --> 01:16:49.100
- Where's the baby? - Where's the baby?

1156
01:16:49.142 --> 01:16:52.563
God damn it! Ain't we got enough to contend with?

1157
01:16:52.605 --> 01:16:54.566
I don't know. ma'am.

1158
01:16:54.608 --> 01:16:57.487
You never leave a man behind!

1159
01:16:57.487 --> 01:17:01.117
Miz McDunnough. I'm worried sick about him!

1160
01:17:01.159 --> 01:17:04.121
Hold on. H.I. Don't be such a hothead!

1161
01:17:04.163 --> 01:17:05.456
H.I.!

1162
01:17:05.498 --> 01:17:07.834
Miz McDunnough!

1163
01:17:07.877 --> 01:17:10.505
-  Let us come with you! -  Please!

1164
01:17:10.547 --> 01:17:12.508
It's our baby. too!

1165
01:17:41.383 --> 01:17:43.427
What is he?

1166
01:17:43.469 --> 01:17:45.597
Do you see him. too?

1167
01:19:04.961 --> 01:19:06.171
Give me that baby!

1168
01:19:07.673 --> 01:19:09.258
I want that baby!

1169
01:19:12.346 --> 01:19:14.974
Give me that baby. you warthog from hell!

1170
01:19:36.839 --> 01:19:39.467
Just lay down on the floor. young missy.

1171
01:19:59.872 --> 01:20:01.123
Run along. now. honey.

1172
01:20:01.166 --> 01:20:02.334
But. Hi...

1173
01:20:03.920 --> 01:20:06.632
Just run along. now. Whoa!

1174
01:22:06.428 --> 01:22:07.971
I'm sorry.

1175
01:23:06.472 --> 01:23:08.600
What the hell's goin' on?

1176
01:23:09.894 --> 01:23:11.479
Get away from there!

1177
01:23:28.712 --> 01:23:30.339
[Whispers] Let's go.

1178
01:23:30.382 --> 01:23:32.843
Wait a minute.

1179
01:23:32.885 --> 01:23:34.554
I ain't through with you.

1180
01:23:35.556 --> 01:23:38.268
What are you doing creeping around here in the dark?

1181
01:23:38.310 --> 01:23:39.436
You in with Smalls?

1182
01:23:39.478 --> 01:23:41.105
Excuse me?

1183
01:23:41.147 --> 01:23:43.525
Leonard Smalls. Big fella.

1184
01:23:43.567 --> 01:23:45.236
Rides a Harley.

1185
01:23:45.278 --> 01:23:46.780
Dresses like a rock star.

1186
01:23:48.825 --> 01:23:52.371
No. sir. That's who we saved him from.

1187
01:23:53.414 --> 01:23:54.707
It's a long story.

1188
01:23:54.750 --> 01:23:56.711
Suppose you tell it.

1189
01:23:56.753 --> 01:24:00.633
Well. sir. in a reward situation...

1190
01:24:00.675 --> 01:24:02.844
they usually say no questions asked.

1191
01:24:04.180 --> 01:24:06.725
Oh...do they?

1192
01:24:06.767 --> 01:24:07.935
Yeah.

1193
01:24:14.862 --> 01:24:16.864
all right. boy.

1194
01:24:19.034 --> 01:24:21.412
I guess you got a reward coming.

1195
01:24:23.124 --> 01:24:25.126
Twenty- five thousand dollars...

1196
01:24:26.211 --> 01:24:30.133
or...if you need home furnishings...

1197
01:24:30.134 --> 01:24:32.637
I can give you a line of credit at any of my stores.

1198
01:24:32.679 --> 01:24:35.725
That's the way I'd rather handle it. Tax reasons.

1199
01:24:35.767 --> 01:24:37.936
We don't want no reward.

1200
01:24:37.978 --> 01:24:39.772
We didn't bring him back for money.

1201
01:24:39.814 --> 01:24:41.399
We could work it that way. too.

1202
01:24:42.651 --> 01:24:46.531
Could I just look at him a little bit more?

1203
01:24:48.201 --> 01:24:49.744
Be my guest. little lady.

1204
01:24:53.333 --> 01:24:54.459
But. uh...

1205
01:24:55.920 --> 01:24:59.049
would...would you mind telling me exactly how you...

1206
01:25:07.687 --> 01:25:10.482
You took him...didn't you?

1207
01:25:11.526 --> 01:25:13.153
Wasn't that biker at all.

1208
01:25:13.195 --> 01:25:15.072
I took him. sir.

1209
01:25:15.115 --> 01:25:17.618
My wife had nothing to do with it.

1210
01:25:17.660 --> 01:25:19.412
I crept in yon window...

1211
01:25:19.454 --> 01:25:20.997
We both did it.

1212
01:25:21.040 --> 01:25:23.209
We didn't want to hurt him any.

1213
01:25:23.251 --> 01:25:24.711
I just wanted to be a mama.

1214
01:25:24.712 --> 01:25:27.549
It wasn't for money or nothing.

1215
01:25:27.591 --> 01:25:31.012
We just figured you had more than you could handle. babywise.

1216
01:25:31.054 --> 01:25:33.766
But I committed the actual crime...

1217
01:25:33.808 --> 01:25:35.769
so if you need to call the authorities...

1218
01:25:35.811 --> 01:25:38.314
Shut up. boy. Nobody's calling the authorities...

1219
01:25:38.356 --> 01:25:39.440
since there's no harm done.

1220
01:25:39.483 --> 01:25:40.609
Thank you. sir.

1221
01:25:40.651 --> 01:25:43.989
Bullshit. Just tell me why you did it.

1222
01:25:47.411 --> 01:25:48.621
We...

1223
01:25:50.498 --> 01:25:52.208
can't have one of our own.

1224
01:25:59.177 --> 01:26:04.142
look. if you can't have kids. you just got to keep trying...

1225
01:26:04.185 --> 01:26:07.105
and hope medical science catches up with you...

1226
01:26:07.105 --> 01:26:08.815
like Florence and me.

1227
01:26:09.985 --> 01:26:11.612
Caught up with a vengeance.

1228
01:26:12.947 --> 01:26:16.744
But. hell. even if it never does for you...

1229
01:26:16.786 --> 01:26:19.373
you still got each other.

1230
01:26:20.374 --> 01:26:24.588
Sir...those are kind words. but...

1231
01:26:24.631 --> 01:26:28.887
I think the wife and I are splitting up.

1232
01:26:28.928 --> 01:26:31.473
Her point is that we're both kind of...

1233
01:26:32.308 --> 01:26:34.394
selfish and unrealistic...

1234
01:26:34.436 --> 01:26:37.315
so we ain't too good for each other.

1235
01:26:38.025 --> 01:26:41.905
Well. ma'am. I don't know much...

1236
01:26:41.947 --> 01:26:43.616
but I do know human beings.

1237
01:26:45.118 --> 01:26:47.120
You brought back my boy...

1238
01:26:47.163 --> 01:26:51.001
so...you must have your good points. too.

1239
01:26:54.715 --> 01:26:57.302
Sure hate to think of Florence leaving me.

1240
01:26:59.138 --> 01:27:03.310
I...do...love her so.

1241
01:27:12.741 --> 01:27:15.995
You can go out the way you came in...

1242
01:27:16.037 --> 01:27:19.792
and before you go off and do another foolish thing...

1243
01:27:19.834 --> 01:27:22.087
like bustin' up...

1244
01:27:22.129 --> 01:27:24.590
I suggest you sleep on it...

1245
01:27:25.968 --> 01:27:27.511
at least one night.

1246
01:27:30.099 --> 01:27:32.852
That night I had a dream.

1247
01:27:33.729 --> 01:27:36.399
I dreamt I was as light as the ether...

1248
01:27:37.860 --> 01:27:41.114
a floating spirit visiting things to come.

1249
01:27:42.742 --> 01:27:46.038
The shades and shadows of the people in my life...

1250
01:27:46.080 --> 01:27:48.500
rassled their way into my slumber.

1251
01:27:50.461 --> 01:27:54.508
I dreamt that Gale and Evelle had decided to return to prison.

1252
01:27:54.551 --> 01:27:56.887
Probably that's just as well.

1253
01:27:56.929 --> 01:27:58.681
I don't mean to sound superior...

1254
01:27:58.723 --> 01:28:01.769
and they're a swell couple guys...

1255
01:28:02.646 --> 01:28:06.151
but maybe they weren't ready yet to come out into the world.

1256
01:28:08.487 --> 01:28:11.032
And then I dreamed on...

1257
01:28:11.074 --> 01:28:12.784
into the future...

1258
01:28:13.745 --> 01:28:16.707
to a Christmas morn in the Arizona home...

1259
01:28:17.584 --> 01:28:20.171
where Nathan Junior was opening a present...

1260
01:28:20.212 --> 01:28:22.214
from a kindly couple...

1261
01:28:22.299 --> 01:28:24.510
who preferred to remain unknown.

1262
01:28:26.889 --> 01:28:29.893
I saw Glen a few years later...

1263
01:28:29.976 --> 01:28:32.729
still having no luck getting the cops to listen...

1264
01:28:32.772 --> 01:28:35.442
to his wild tales about me and Ed.

1265
01:28:37.529 --> 01:28:40.700
Maybe he threw in one Polack joke too many.

1266
01:28:41.493 --> 01:28:43.287
I don't know.

1267
01:28:45.123 --> 01:28:47.584
And still I dreamed on...

1268
01:28:48.378 --> 01:28:52.634
further into the future than I'd ever dreamed before...

1269
01:28:53.802 --> 01:28:56.973
watching Nathan Junior's progress from afar...

1270
01:28:58.016 --> 01:29:01.771
taking pride in his accomplishments...

1271
01:29:01.813 --> 01:29:03.440
as if he were our own...

1272
01:29:04.484 --> 01:29:07.989
wondering if he ever thought of us...

1273
01:29:08.782 --> 01:29:12.620
and hoping maybe we'd broadened his horizons a little...

1274
01:29:13.497 --> 01:29:16.835
even if he couldn't remember just how they got broadened.

1275
01:29:19.255 --> 01:29:22.760
But still I hadn't dreamt nothing about me and Ed...

1276
01:29:23.887 --> 01:29:25.305
until the end.

1277
01:29:26.766 --> 01:29:28.476
And this was cloudier...

1278
01:29:29.311 --> 01:29:33.525
'cause it was years... years away...

1279
01:29:35.612 --> 01:29:39.367
but I saw an old couple being visited by their children...

1280
01:29:40.243 --> 01:29:42.412
and all their grandchildren. too.

1281
01:29:43.915 --> 01:29:46.376
The old couple wasn't screwed up...

1282
01:29:47.420 --> 01:29:51.008
and neither were their kids or their grandkids.

1283
01:29:51.050 --> 01:29:52.677
Dad.

1284
01:29:52.720 --> 01:29:56.767
And I don't know. You tell me.

1285
01:29:57.601 --> 01:29:59.144
This whole dream...

1286
01:30:00.689 --> 01:30:02.483
was it wishful thinking?

1287
01:30:03.652 --> 01:30:09.201
Was I just fleeing reality like I know I'm liable to do?

1288
01:30:10.328 --> 01:30:11.663
But me and Ed...

1289
01:30:13.541 --> 01:30:15.210
we can be good. too.

1290
01:30:16.545 --> 01:30:18.255
And it seemed real.

1291
01:30:20.008 --> 01:30:21.927
It seemed like us...

1292
01:30:22.679 --> 01:30:24.139
and it seemed like...

1293
01:30:26.935 --> 01:30:28.270
our home.

1294
01:30:30.148 --> 01:30:34.988
If not Arizona. then a land not too far away...

1295
01:30:36.407 --> 01:30:40.537
where all parents are strong and wise and capable...

1296
01:30:41.581 --> 01:30:44.460
and all children are happy and beloved.

1297
01:30:46.713 --> 01:30:47.923
I don't know.

1298
01:30:50.594 --> 01:30:52.263
Maybe it was Utah.

